<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1852] Fix remaining localization test failures in lucene</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1852</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;see also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1836&quot; title=&quot;Flexible QueryParser fails with local different from en_US&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1836&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1846&quot; title=&quot;More Locale problems in Lucene&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1846&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;all tests should pass under different locales.&lt;br/&gt;
the fix is to run &apos;ant test&apos; under different locales, look and fix problems, and use the LocalizedTestCase from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1836&quot; title=&quot;Flexible QueryParser fails with local different from en_US&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1836&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to keep them from coming back.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the same approach as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1836&quot; title=&quot;Flexible QueryParser fails with local different from en_US&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1836&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixes the core queryparser, but I am running ant test under a few locales to look for more problems.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
